metadata.name: Arrows Between Emotions #76
metadata.description:
The project “Arrows Between Emotions” was formed with a concern to present this transformation in an artist and code developer, making the logic appear through precise and well-defined forms, but that the stage was really of emotions through freer curves involving aligned with accentuated movements in directions of straight or oblique ascents and even in more circular or decadent processes that are part of the journey of the wheel of life of art and the artist.


The process of the work involved the construction of a background to receive the shapes and colors. I used an algorithm that generated a distribution of noise across the screen, with its coloring related to the shapes in the search for a pleasant composition. Then came the objective forms, setting the stage, finally, for the flow of emotions through the agglutinated and dispersed curves soaked in colors in a game of shadow and light, presenting the depth and movement of the creation process and the orientation to which it takes. all the strength of this walk.

Press 's' key in live mode to save in png.

license: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0
@pixelflowart, May 2022

metadata.name: fx_doughs #6214
The Song Of Colors #50
metadata.description:
Watercolor painting was my favorite technique for playing. I love combining colors, merging and blending them together. Furthermore, I started experimenting with large pieces of canvas, placed them at different heights, and poured vast layers of acrylic fluid paint on them.
The energy of these paintings is incredible. As I layer the colors, the colors begin to converse. It seems to have the color of its own mind.
I started with an image in mind, but always, painting takes over everything. Using canvas installed at different heights requires careful thinking and planning in advance. Sometimes the color goes into a new shape that I did not expect, but I correct it and use it to the fullest. This kind of art creates exciting and psychological paintings!
Color flow is instantaneous. I am constantly spinning around the canvas and directing the flow; there is no time but to go with the flow. I started as a guide, but I know that I've just been an active agent - letting the song of colors sing and flow.
- Press "S" to save an artwork.
- Collectors who own this NFT have the right to print the work.
Made with p5js.

metadata.name: Shift #241
metadata.description:
A generative algorithm honing the power of vertical displacement.

How simple may a generative algorithm be while simultaneously staying diverse enough for each art piece to be truly unique? Shift is the result of an exploration into this space, basing its existence on two principles — dissection and vertical shifting. Each variable in this art engine has been meticulously weighted, giving rise to high diversity and the possibility of epic combinations. 

Shift is a series of 888 unique pieces.

############

Display resolution is 1000x1400. Press ’s’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x8400 hi-res image. This may take a while to generate depending on your hardware.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022

metadata.name: Heavy Light #21
metadata.description:
This is an experiment in spaces lit by falling particles of light.

Each particle draws a thin trace as it falls and changes its colour whenever it reflects from a wall or an obstacle. 

The piece takes some time to fully render. After the signature appears on the bottom of the picture, you are free to hit 's' to save a high resolution PNG for printing and seeing the finer details.

The work features 5 different canvas sizes and 8 palettes.

metadata.name: fx_doughs #463
Gardens of delusion #81
metadata.description:
We live in a perpetual state of assertive belief, and the outside world never faults us, because we escape contradiction through a process of delusion. How reassuring it is to wander in the alleys of subjectivity and take a seat to look at these gardens we create.

Click to play the audio track.
You can zoom in/out, drag and pan.
Press « A » to toggle the autoplay mode that will change the scene every 600 frames.
Press the space bar to download a screenshot of the current frame :
- width : 4096px
- height : based on ratio
- file format : PNG

metadata.name: Grove #129
metadata.description:
A generative, impressionist painting of a small grove of trees in one of the four seasons. In spring and summer, flowers bloom in the meadow. A rare variation will create a charcoal drawing on white or black paper. Super rare will create a lighted winter scene that may have a moon behind the tree.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.

Press 's' to save a screenshot at any point. Image size is 1400x1082px.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 3,000 px.

On the paintings only, adding '&bg=true' will stop the painting after the background. Adding '&size=3000&bg=true' will give you a nice desktop background! 

Common Features:
- About 12-14 trees
- One of the four seasons
- One of 12 highlight color tints
- One of 12 shadow color tints
- Varying levels of distance haze
- Varying max brush sizes
- Varying amount of colors in the strokes

Less Common
- 15% chance of a charcoal drawing
- 50% chance it to be a dark winter scene

Rare
- Winter drawing with lights on the tree

Super Rare
- Winter drawing with a moon behind the tree

metadata.name: Maps of Life #55
metadata.description:
Maps of Life is a generative cartographic experiment inspired by John Conway's Game of Life. The Game of Life is a zero-player game, its evolution is determined by its initial state, requiring no further input.

Maps of Life is a generative-player game, an algorithm that creates an initial random configuration and a collector that observes how the configuration evolves. Each mint produces a distinctly unique cartographic representation of an ideal town, with different color palettes, scales, and coordinates, an animation from its random birth to a stopped moment in time.

Maps of Life assumes that the built environment has a life of its own. And besides, only an automatic mind can name towns with Butterfly Names. Enjoy the view.

---
Interactivity:
Press LEFT and RIGHT arrows to speed-up or slow-down the evolution of the town.
Press "S" to save the current state to a PNG image.
If you want to change the resolution, just add "?res=XXX" to the end of the url.
---

(With these keys, you can possibly force the script to continue until its further completion. Could you get a deserted landscape?)
